      <item>
        <title>Pull data from wordpress page</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[Johan]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>I have different types of pages, so each of them has its own component (or is shared):</p>
<pre><code class="lang-html">&lt;Switch&gt;
   &lt;Loading when={data.isFetching} /&gt;
   &lt;Single when={data.isHome} isHome="true" /&gt;
   &lt;Blog when={data.isArchive} /&gt;
   &lt;Article when={data.isPost} /&gt;
   &lt;Single when={data.isPage} /&gt;
   &lt;PageError when={data.isError} /&gt;
   &lt;Jobs when={data.isAwsmJobOpeningsArchive} /&gt;
   &lt;Job when={data.isAwsmJobOpenings} /&gt;
&lt;/Switch&gt;
</code></pre>
<p>Which is because some content types have different elements to handle, besides the fact I want to have full control of how stuff looks.<br>
Technically you should be able to handle a page through the Post component:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-html">&lt;Post when={data.isPage} /&gt;
</code></pre>
          <p><a href="https://community.frontity.org/t/pull-data-from-wordpress-page/4698/7">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
